Definitely would considered this place an unassuming neighborhood gem. I lived in this area for many years and always wanted to visit and never went. Mainly due to laziness as this place was use to be cash only. So I decided to have dinner while I was in town with a friend. I was really blown away at how extensive the menu was which I really appreciated. I've been to other Italian spots in the neighborhood and wasn't particularly impressed with the menu. Anything Italian was on Gersi menu. We decided for starters to get the brussel sprouts and some other offers which was pretty good. We settled on the cacio pepe and papperdelle with bologense sauce. The portions were huge, hearty and tasty. We definitely had to get doggy bags. We decided to order some red wine and that was really tasty. We ended the night with some tiramisu. Now I will say....I'm a tiramisu stan. This tiramisu was 5/5. It was moist and you really got a taste of the espresso as well as the cream. PHENOMENAL. The only thing that was a little annoying was the outside seating which OBVIOUSLY is really out of their hands. So i will end this review by stating SUPPORT SMALL BUSINESSES! especially gems as these. Looking forward to coming here next time I'm in town.

This restaurant deserves an A+ across the charts. A week prior to a birthday celebration, I spent countless of hours researching to find a restaurant with backyard dining that would accommodate our party size on such short notice during Covid. Thanks to Resy, I discovered Gersi. I immediately contacted Gersi and spoke with a gentleman by the name of Douglas, we spoke about my plans and he booked the reservation for me right away on Resy. I called several times thoughout the week to solidify small details and Douglas displayed eagerness to help each time. The food was great, drinks were awesome,  scenery wonderful. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS PLACE.

I am so glad we chose Gersi for one of our first outdoor dining experiences. Four of us ate at their outdoor dining area on the street and we were the only people there. This made it more comfortable for us, but I wish we chose the spacious backyard instead. If you're reading this, definitely ask for the backyard space!  I had to try the spaghetti al limone - I've never heard of a dish like this before and with the hot, humid weather we've been experiencing the idea of refreshing citrus won me over. This dish did not disappoint! Every bite had a perfect mix of crisp lemon, creamy cheese, and pasta. I'm not sure if they make their pasta in-house or not, but the texture of the spaghetti was absolutely perfect with just enough chew.  My friends got the carbonera, which was also excellent, and the black linguini. I appreciate that Gersi gave bread and oil before the food came, margins are tight these days and that gesture went a long way (the bread was tasty too).  Great choice for takeout or delivery or outdoor dining. I need to come back to visit the backyard!

we arrived 3 minutes before our reservation and the host informed us there would be a 20 minute wait. he was immediately defensive, dismissive and not apologetic in the slightest, and seemed annoyed that we were frustrated. i was taking my boyfriend out to celebrate his birthday and made a reservation so that we wouldn’t have to wait 20 minutes for a table.  against our better judgment, we waited and had a mediocre meal. the server was much nicer than the host, but the drinks we ordered never came. the squid ink pasta was ok, the chicken parm was good for a few bites but lacked flavor, which made it hard to get through the giant portion. the real kicker was that our meals made both of us sick for the rest of the night—we each had an appetizer and main and did not share, so it’s unlikely that just one dish was the culprit.  we definitely paid the price for not trusting our guts—should have walked away when we ran into trouble at the door. if a restaurant can’t honor reservations, they shouldn’t take them.

Gersi is the most AMAZING Italian restaurant in New York! My husband and I traveled up to New York from Virginia for the weekend and my #1 request was that enjoy an authentic nice Italian dinner....and this place was just that. Everything from the atmosphere, to the service, to the food and drinks was above and beyond my expectations. First, the atmosphere: it's a cute little upscale bistro where all of the tables and chairs are different, yet still seem to match and give you that Italian country-side feel. The renovation the owners did on the space is definitely noticeable. The wallpaper is subtle, yet classy. The chandeliers add a nice touch of bling and elegance and the patio outback makes you feel like you're no where close to a city. Second, the service: from the host, to the runner, to the bartender, server, manager, and even chef...everyone was so friendly and inviting. They gave you that homey feel where you could carry on a conversation with them for hours. My water glass was never below half-full, the pace of the dinner was perfect! My biggest pet-peeve is when your multiple courses come out too close together and then your table is crowded, this never happened with our several courses...great service! Third, the food and drinks: after ordering, the server brought us out some fresh Italian bread with a white bean bruschetta (I've never had this before, but it was so unique and delicious...beats the typical olive oil dip and butter). My husband and I ordered a mixed greens salad to split. There was a nice blend of different leafy greens and a super light fresh-squeezed lemon vinaigrette, which kept the salad light since we had a big dinner coming up. I ordered the Spaghetti, which had FRESH noodles (yes, you can really taste a difference) Parmesan cheese, and a fresh-squeezed lemon juice. This might sound basic, but it was delicious and light on a such a hot summer night...plus my husband ordered pasta with red sauce, so we shared :) My husband ordered the bolognese pasta (also with fresh pasta noodles). The sauce was the perfect balance of meat to sauce to pasta ratio and was by far the best bolognese sauce I've ever had. The portion sizes were perfect too...not too much that you leave bloated, but you definitely don't leave hungry either! After dinner we ordered to dessert to take home with us...the Panna Cotta and Tiramisu...both were divine and also great portions...and they even used fresh whipped cream! As for my drink, I told my server (Mohammad) that I would like a glass of dry red wine, but to surprise me because I didn't know any of these wines on the list....he nailed it...great glass of wine to complement my amazing dinner. The best part about all of this is that we didn't break the bank to enjoy such a fabulous multi-course dinner. The prices are very reasonable for such FRESH Italian food in Brooklyn! If you're staying in the city, this place is definitely worth the cab/subway ride to try and enjoy...you won't regret it :)
